 Category 3: Liskov Substitution Violations in BaseService (6 errors)

  Problem: TranscriptionService and TranscriptProcessorService inherit from BaseService but override methods with incompatible signatures:

  | BaseService                | TranscriptionService                                       |
  |----------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
  | create(entity: T)          | create(request: TranscriptionCreateRequest, user_uid: str) |
  | update(uid, updates: dict) | update(uid, request: TranscriptionUpdateRequest)           |
  | delete(uid, cascade=False) | delete(uid)                                                |

  Design Lesson: These services are NOT Activity Domains (per CLAUDE.md). They're Content/Processing domains that shouldn't inherit from BaseService.

  Recommendation: Make TranscriptionService and TranscriptProcessorService standalone facades like JournalsService. They don't fit the Activity Domain contract.
